<section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-800 via-green-900/20 to-gray-800 relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Background Pattern -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-5">
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 1px 1px, rgba(34,197,94,0.3) 1px, transparent 0); background-size: 28px 28px;"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 via-teal-400 to-cyan-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
        Installation Guide
      </h2>
      <div class="w-32 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-cyan-400 mx-auto rounded-full mb-6"></div>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        How to Download And Install Jenny Mod on PC?
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg mb-8 text-center">
        After Downloading It, You Need to follow the following step to Install this Add-on in your Minecraft Universe:
      </p>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 1:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Find a reputable source like <a href="/" class="text-blue-300 hover:text-blue-200 underline">www.jennymod.dev</a> to download the MOD. It is important to make sure you are downloading it from a trusted website like ours, as some versions of Jenny Mod may contain viruses or other harmful components.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 2:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Click on the download link for the latest version of Jenny Minecraft Mod. Make sure the version is compatible with your Windows PC.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 3:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            After Downloading this mod You need to Download and Install Forge for Install this Mod On Your Minecraft Game.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 4:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            After downloading and installing the Forge app, open it up and create a custom profile. Name the profile whatever you like and make sure to select the Jenny Mod version.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 5:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            After creating the custom profile, navigate to your downloads folder and copy the mod file that you have downloaded.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 6:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Go back to the Forge app and click on the customer profile that you created earlier. Click on the "Open Folder" button to open up the folder where the mod files should be placed.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 7:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Once you are in the folder, paste the file.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 8:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Launch Minecraft using the CurseForge app and create a new single-player world.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-teal-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-3">Step 9:</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Once you are in the world, type in "Jenny" in the search bar and she should spawn in the world. Enjoy playing with the Jenny Mod!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>